# Left 4 Dead (2008) Reverse-Engineered Source Code

This project is a fully reverse-engineered recreation of Left 4 Dead (2008) by Valve. Built from scratch, it aims to provide insight into the inner workings of the game while preserving its legacy.

## Disclaimer
This project is a clean-room reverse engineering effort and does not contain any leaked or proprietary Valve code. It is intended for educational and research purposes only.

## Features
- Faithful recreation of Left 4 Dead's core mechanics
- Source-compatible engine modifications
- Multiplayer and AI behavior replication
- Tools and utilities for modding and debugging

## Requirements
- Source SDK (depending on your target engine)
- A legal copy of Left 4 Dead for assets
- A compiler supporting C++

## Building
1. Clone the repository:
   ```sh
   git clone
   ```
2. Install dependencies as listed in `docs/requirements.txt` (if applicable).
3. Compile the source code using your preferred toolchain.
4. Place the required game assets in the appropriate directories.

